name: IWD 2018 - GDG Jaipur

venue.name: Academic Block
venue.address_1: The LNM Institute of Information Technology
venue.address_2: Rupa Ki Nangal, Post Sumel, Via Jamdoli

description:
• What we'll do
We are proud to be hosting the our IWD event to mark the celebration of the 2018 International Women's Day. This event will highlight the stories of our growing female community of designers, developers, and technology entrepreneurs.
(Click here to learn more: https://www.womentechmakers.com/iwd18 )

The event will primarily focus on women participation. You will experience a fun-filled mixture of tech sessions, women inspiring stories, DIY activities, quiz etc.

You get goodies to take back home. Food and beverage is on us!

• What to bring
Passion to learn!

AGENDA:
10am: Registrations begin
10:30am: Opening Remarks and KeyNote
11:00am: Session on BlockChain and Cryptocurrency with Hands on Activity
12:00pm: Session on Android Development and Git with CodeLab
1-2pm: Lunch and Networking Session
2pm: TechQuiz
2:30pm: Session on Google Summer of Code
3:30pm: Session on Outreachy
4pm: Thank you Note and Feedback
4:30-5pm: Reception and Good Night!

name: International Women's Day Summit 2019 by WTM,Jaipur & FDC, Jaipur
description:
From Ada Lovelace to Grace Hopper to thousands of Googlers, we're proud of the contributions women in technology have made across our industry and across our company and we're excited by the contributions women continue to make today. International Women's Day is an important moment to recognize how women have influenced the tech industry and beyond and to celebrate this , Women Techmakers Jaipur in association with Facebook Developer Circle, Jaipur is hosting International Women's Day Summit 2019.
IWD 2019 Theme: Lift as you climb
Date: 31st March 2019
Venue : Arch College of Design and Business,
Plot No. 9, Govind Marg, Block-B, Institutional Area, Malviya Nagar,
Jaipur, Rajasthan[masked]

Registration is mandatory.

Registeration form :
https://iwdsummit.splashthat.com/

(Agenda and Final List of speakers will be updated soon)
The event is open to all, but we would encourage more women to be a part of this celebration!

If you know any potential speakers , please refer them
Call for Speakers : https://forms.gle/9isLG2JddLMp6My48

To make our event more engaging and to help us support future exciting meetups, we would really appreciate collaborations/sponsorships.
Sponsorship/Collaboration form : https://forms.gle/GJQeqbYjf3ggTBkW6
